# TableCardView

## Summary

Renders a table-number card: an optional uppercase event-title kicker, the table name in large serif type, and an optional italic accent line. Like PlaceCardView it is the single source of truth for the stationery — the TableCard card definition and the planner's print sheet both render it, so print output matches the card exactly. Container-query sizing lets it scale from an isolated card down to a print-sheet cell.

## Import

```js
import { TableCardView } from '../components/card-views';
```

## Template Usage

As rendered on the planner's print sheet (all args optional; the name falls back to "Table"):

```gjs
<TableCardView
  @eventTitle={{@model.eventTitle}}
  @tableName={{t.name}}
  @accent={{@model.venue}}
/>
```
